Description: I am selling my Line 6 JTV-89. This guitar is a few years old, but has never been played out of the house. I am not a dealer. No chips or dings that I can see, all of the electronics are perfect. Comes with the battery and charger (both work perfectly), and the gig bag, which is also in like new condition. This is such an incredible guitar, between all of the different tones that it models (strat/tele/les paul/firebird/explorer/acoustics/12 string/sitar, goes on and on), and the tuning functionality, it's the most versatile guitar I've ever seen. The JTV-89 is the "shredder" model of the series, with 24 frets, a very fast slim profile neck, and built in tunings that are geared towards shredder type tunings (drop d, d, c, etc). I'm selling this because I don't play guitar in a band anymore, and I just don't have the time to play it, so I'd like to see it go to somebody that will put it to great use. I can take more pics if you need, just shoot me an email. Shipping to lower 48 states only, or local pickup on Long Island. I will accept Paypal only. I will leave positive feedback for the winning bidder once the transaction is complete, and I will ship within 1 business day of the transaction closing (shipping via UPS). Good luck!
Title: Line 6 JTV-89 James Tyler Variax Guitar - Almost Perfect Condition, Never Gigged
